    Also all that area, containing by admeasurement one and a half perches, being a square piece of land at the Magnetic Station, Doubtless Bay, in Section 146, Parish of Mangonui, one side of the square being part of the southern side of the road along the seashore forming the northern boundary of the said Section 146, the opposite side being a line parallel to and 30.3 links distant from the southern side of the said road, and the other two sides at right angles to the southern side of the said road and running through points distant 15.15 links from the centre of the magnetic station:
    
    As the same are delineated on the plan marked L and S 51527, deposited in the Head Office, Department of Lands and Survey, at Wellington, and thereon coloured red.
    
