    (2) The land to which this section relates is more particularly described as follows:---
    
    All that parcel of land, containing fourteen perches, more or less, being part of the Port Chalmers Town Belt, bounded as follows: on the south-east 80 links, south-west 75 links, and the north-west 105 links, by the aforesaid Town Belt; and on the north-east 40 links by railway reserve, and 100 links by new cemetery: be all the aforesaid linkages more or less: as the same is delineated on the plan marked L and S 2/343, deposited in the Head Office, Department of Lands and Survey, at Wellington, and thereon edged red.
    
    The Cemeteries Act 1908 (1908 No 19) was repealed, as from 1 April 1965, by section [61(1)][174] Burial and Cremation Act 1964 (1964 No 75).

